            <fr:anchor>369</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-002I</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-002I.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Banach Space">Banach Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A Banach space is a complete <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002K.xml" addr="FA-002K" title="Normed Space">normed space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>A normed space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is called a Banach space if every <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002L.xml" addr="FA-002L" title="Cauchy sequence">Cauchy sequence</fr:link> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> converges to an element in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>370</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-002J</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-002J.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Hilbert Space">Hilbert Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A Hilbert space is a complete <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002M.xml" addr="FA-002M" title="Inner Product">inner product space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Hilbert spaces extend the methods of vector algebra and calculus from 2D and 3D Euclidean spaces to spaces with any finite or infinite number of dimensions.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Key properties include:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>Every Hilbert space is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002I.xml" addr="FA-002I" title="Banach Space">Banach space</fr:link>, with the norm derived from the inner product</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:link type="local" href="FA-002N.xml" addr="FA-002N" title="Orthonormal Basis">Orthonormal basis</fr:link> existence</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:link type="local" href="FA-002O.xml" addr="FA-002O" title="Projection Theorem">Projection theorem</fr:link></fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>371</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-002H</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-002H.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Linear Operator">Linear Operator</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A linear operator is a mapping between vector spaces that preserves the operations of addition and scalar multiplication.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> be vector spaces over a field <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex>. A mapping <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[T: X \rightarrow  Y]]></fr:tex> is a linear operator if:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[T(x + y) = T(x) + T(y)]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x, y \in  X]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[T(\alpha  x) = \alpha  T(x)]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \alpha  \in  K]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
  </fr:backmatter>
